TITLE/EDITION Advanced Assessment: Interpreting Findings and Formulating Differential Diagnoses
Author: Mary Jo Goolsby EdD MSN ANP-C CAE FAANP (Author), Laurie Grubbs PhD MSN ANP-C (Author)
Paperback: 672 pages
Publisher: F.A. Davis Company; 3 edition (November 14, 2014)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 0803643632
ISBN-13: 978-0803643635
NOTE: This is the standalone ebook and may not include access codes that come packaged with the bound book

_____________________________________________________________________________________


The 3rd Edition of this AJN Book of the Year shows you how to perform a focused history and physical based on presenting complaints and then interpret the findings to arrive at a definitive differential diagnosis.

Its complaint-focused organization makes it the perfect point-of-care resource for the classroom and in the clinical setting
